References:-
https://developer.hashicorp.com/consul/docs/secure/encryption/tls/enable/existing/vm#configure-the-clients
https://developer.hashicorp.com/consul/commands/tls/cert

Deploy 2 VMs on multipass.

Install Consul on both the VMs https://developer.hashicorp.com/consul/install
On first VM (consul-server) run below commands:-
consul tls ca create
consul tls cert create -server

Run consul :-
nohup consul agent -config-file=consul-server.hcl &
export CONSUL_HTTP_ADDR=https://127.0.0.1:8501
export CONSUL_HTTP_SSL_VERIFY=false
consul members
consul operator raft list-peers

Copy ca file from first VM to your system
multipass transfer intriguing-planarian:/home/ubuntu/consul-agent-ca.pem .
Copy ca file from your system to second VM (consul-client)
multipass transfer consul-agent-ca.pem tasty-darter:/home/ubuntu/

Run consul client on VM2:-
nohup consul agent -config-file=consul-client.hcl &
export CONSUL_HTTP_ADDR=https://127.0.0.1:8501
export CONSUL_HTTP_SSL_VERIFY=false
consul members

